4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a fee is required to record
6 certain mortgages, deeds of trust, contracts of
7 conditional sale, or other similar instruments given to
8 secure the payment of any debt which conveys any real
9 or personal property.
10 This bill would increase the fee for recording
11 of certain mortgages, deeds of trust, contracts of
12 conditional sale, or similar instruments given to
13 secure the payment of any debt which conveys any real
14 or personal property.
15 This bill would modify the rate and distribution
16 of the mortgage record tax in order to provide a
17 dedicated revenue for the Alabama Housing Trust Fund.
18 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
19 technical revisions to update the existing code
20 language to current style.
21
22
23 A BILL
24 TO BE ENTITLED
25 AN ACT
